README.md
     1→# Toasty
     3→**Current status: Incubating - Toasty is not ready for production usage. The API
     4→is still evolving and documentation is lacking.**
     5→
     6→Toasty is an ORM for the Rust programming language that prioritizes ease-of-use.
     7→It supports both SQL databases as well as some NoSQL databases, including DynamoDB
     8→and Cassandra. Note that Toasty does not hide the database capabilities.
     9→Instead, Toasty exposes features based on the target database.
    10→
    11→## Using Toasty
    76→## SQL and NoSQL
    91→## Application data model vs. database schema
    98→## Current status and roadmap
   117→### Contribution

